1
00:00:03,320 --> 00:00:05,760
Come on, babe, you're not that pathetic.
-I'm gonna die.

2
00:00:05,840 --> 00:00:07,360
You sound just like Mom.

3
00:00:07,520 --> 00:00:10,240
I feel that sting right here,
you know it's coming.

4
00:00:10,320 --> 00:00:12,320
Okay, fine, come on, you can fight it.

5
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:13,680
No, it's pointless.
-I don't get it.

6
00:00:13,760 --> 00:00:15,640
Why is it that whenever you guys are sick, you're all dying?

7
00:00:16,360 --> 00:00:17,720
And I'm not talking about your ethnicity,

8
00:00:17,800 --> 00:00:19,120
I'm talking about the whole gender thing.

9
00:00:19,400 --> 00:00:22,960
Babe, maybe it's that new flu
that's going around this week.

10
00:00:23,480 --> 00:00:26,560
And I'm the first victim here in the country?
-What a Shakespeare.

11
00:00:27,040 --> 00:00:28,400
Molière
-What?

12
00:00:28,520 --> 00:00:29,720
Molière wrote "The Imaginary Invalid."

13
00:00:30,320 --> 00:00:32,360
No, I meant your Shakespearean drama.

14
00:00:32,960 --> 00:00:35,760
But you just opened a whole new topic here.

15
00:00:36,240 --> 00:00:38,560
The Imaginary Invalid?
-No. No topic, no...

16
00:00:38,720 --> 00:00:40,520
You don't believe me. Put your hand on your forehead,

17
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:41,760
you're getting a third-degree burn.

18
00:00:42,720 --> 00:00:45,600
Oh, what nonsense. It's nothing,
it's not serious at all, you don't have a fever.

19
00:00:46,240 --> 00:00:48,560
I might infect your family.
They'll all blame me.

20
00:00:48,640 --> 00:00:50,200
First of all, I'm taking responsibility for this. Okay?

21
00:00:50,280 --> 00:00:54,680
And secondly, in my family, we don't get so worked up
about illnesses like in your family.

22
00:00:55,160 --> 00:00:57,640
And if they haven't lost you by now,
trust me, they won't lose you today either.

23
00:00:57,720 --> 00:01:00,720
And don't forget we're a vaccinated family.
-How vaccinated?

24
00:01:00,800 --> 00:01:03,120
Strong. The Hasson family, vaccinated.

25
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:05,040
Strong.

26
00:01:08,960 --> 00:01:11,480
Look at me, look at me and...

27
00:01:19,960 --> 00:01:22,280
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

28
00:01:22,360 --> 00:01:25,240
Oh, Shabbat Shalom. Shabbat Shalom, Shabbat Shalom.

29
00:01:25,720 --> 00:01:27,360
What's up, Dad?
-All good.

30
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:30,640
Sitting with Pharaoh! Trying to fix the computer.

31
00:01:30,720 --> 00:01:33,360
Pharaoh, Pharaoh, Pharaoh.

32
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:35,760
What, talking to Efrat today?
-Shabbat Shalom.

33
00:01:37,040 --> 00:01:39,120
What's wrong with you, are you sick? Really?

34
00:01:39,200 --> 00:01:43,160
Yeah, Dad, Shai's like me. When he has a cold
he's in total system failure,

35
00:01:43,240 --> 00:01:45,000
he's dying like crazy. He came here for

36
00:01:45,080 --> 00:01:47,600
his last supper.
-You're just exaggerating.

37
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:52,480
Exaggerating, exaggerating, but I'm asking you
to stay away from me, please.

38
00:01:52,560 --> 00:01:54,240
I wanted you to help me with the computer but I'd rather

39
00:01:54,320 --> 00:01:57,280
you keep my space sterile.

40
00:01:57,360 --> 00:02:00,920
I didn't know you were this hysterical.
-You told me the Hassons are vaccinated,

41
00:02:01,160 --> 00:02:05,160
they have immunity...
-Just this week they talked on TV

42
00:02:05,240 --> 00:02:09,400
about an outbreak, Adobe.
They talked about families of viruses.

43
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:12,080
For you, every virus is the size of a cockroach.

44
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:14,520
Sit down, I'm going home.

45
00:02:14,680 --> 00:02:16,480
No, you don't need to go home. Why home?

46
00:02:16,880 --> 00:02:19,160
Go to the kitchen, why are you standing here, go to the kitchen.

47
00:02:19,240 --> 00:02:20,320
Great idea.

48
00:02:21,280 --> 00:02:25,480
Dad, what's wrong, come?
-What?

49
00:02:25,840 --> 00:02:27,840
Where's Mom?
-She's on a wrap-up call with Meirav.

50
00:02:27,920 --> 00:02:30,240
Why a wrap-up?
-Meirav is going abroad,

51
00:02:30,320 --> 00:02:32,360
so she's having wrap-up calls with all the family members.

52
00:02:32,440 --> 00:02:34,000
She started with your mom.

53
00:02:34,600 --> 00:02:37,800
Mom, I'm going with Orna to Hollywood,

54
00:02:38,160 --> 00:02:42,720
I don't know if I'll come back with her
after a week because there's a bigger chance

55
00:02:43,040 --> 00:02:48,080
I'll find a Hollywood husband
and stay there forever, like, forever.

56
00:02:48,480 --> 00:02:50,440
Meirav, have you lost it?

57
00:02:50,560 --> 00:02:52,000
What, you think it's easy to find a husband in Hollywood?

58
00:02:52,080 --> 00:02:54,760
Well, that's not up for discussion, I'm just letting you know.

59
00:02:55,240 --> 00:02:56,880
Besides, it's Hollywood, Mom,

60
00:02:57,120 --> 00:02:58,240
everyone lives in a movie there.

61
00:02:58,320 --> 00:03:00,960
Yeah, in a bad movie, directed by Uri Paster.

62
00:03:01,040 --> 00:03:02,960
What about Efrat?
-Efrat's not an actress.

63
00:03:03,080 --> 00:03:05,240
Her husband’s not an actor, and they actually met here.

64
00:03:05,320 --> 00:03:09,600
Just so you know, you and Dad
never supported what I do,

65
00:03:09,760 --> 00:03:12,520
you always blocked my luck. Everything that happened to me in life

66
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:16,840
happened because of you.
That's why I'm leaving and starting fresh.

67
00:03:17,120 --> 00:03:18,440
Page bio.
-Okay.

68
00:03:19,320 --> 00:03:21,560
Oh, and one more thing. I made a deal with a good friend of mine

69
00:03:21,640 --> 00:03:23,960
that if I don’t come back,
I’ll rent her my room.

70
00:03:24,040 --> 00:03:25,840
What’s that?
-600 dollars a month,

71
00:03:25,920 --> 00:03:28,480
fifty-fifty, it’ll help me cover my stay there

72
00:03:28,600 --> 00:03:30,440
and you guys won’t be bored here either.
-What’s that?

73
00:03:30,520 --> 00:03:32,880
She’ll probably get used to you,
just like I did.

74
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:34,920
But I’m not used to you yet.

75
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:37,280
Well, if you have any objections,

76
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:39,560
it doesn’t matter
because you should have said that

77
00:03:39,640 --> 00:03:43,480
before the deal was closed.
Sorry, now it’s too late.

78
00:03:44,720 --> 00:03:46,840
Ah, it turned out tasty today, right?

79
00:03:46,920 --> 00:03:48,440
I don’t know, I can’t taste anything.

80
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:52,360
All my taste buds are blocked. It’s hard for me to feel.

81
00:03:52,440 --> 00:03:54,640
That’s why the cooks in hospitals don’t invest,

82
00:03:54,720 --> 00:03:55,720
because no one can taste anything.

83
00:03:56,720 --> 00:03:58,600
I’m done.
-I’m done too.

84
00:03:58,680 --> 00:04:00,240
Alright, girls, you can go play now.

85
00:04:00,720 --> 00:04:03,520
Sit, honey, do me a favor, if you love me,

86
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:06,720
