114
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:16,400
Let me know when I can wash the kids.
-I’m coming to deal with the germs.

115
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:18,600
Come on, what did she tell you?

116
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:23,360
That because of us she is what she is?
-Yeah, yeah, also. Of course.

117
00:05:24,120 --> 00:05:27,520
She said that if she stays there
longer than the week she planned,

118
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:30,520
yeah?
-She wants to rent her room

119
00:05:31,120 --> 00:05:32,760
to her friend.
-What?

120
00:05:33,320 --> 00:05:36,520
She’s like a protected tenant,
and she wants to rent her room.

121
00:05:36,600 --> 00:05:41,040
In subletting.
-I have no problem with her staying forever.

122
00:05:41,160 --> 00:05:44,320
Abroad, okay? Just that, she can't,

123
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:46,240
she can't take ownership of...

124
00:05:47,640 --> 00:05:50,760
What did you say? What did you say? That she wants to rent

125
00:05:50,880 --> 00:05:54,400
her room to someone else?
And you're okay with a stranger

126
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:57,520
living in our house?
-Don't worry, I'll handle it.

127
00:05:57,840 --> 00:05:58,680
It was fine.

128
00:06:00,640 --> 00:06:05,280
Between us, Sali, it can't get worse
than the current tenant.

129
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:08,520
What's true is true.
-True.

130
00:06:10,320 --> 00:06:12,560
Manny, you're in a hugging frenzy.
-Yeah, talk to me when you hit 39.4.

131
00:06:12,640 --> 00:06:15,720
Three days in a row.
-Hey, how are you feeling, sweetheart?

132
00:06:15,840 --> 00:06:17,640
I'm fine, oh my, the man on his deathbed.

133
00:06:18,080 --> 00:06:20,840
Shai, are you okay? How are you feeling?

134
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:23,560
Thank you very much.
-Honey, do you want me to put something on your plate?

135
00:06:23,640 --> 00:06:26,840
I won't eat until Shai finishes.
I don't want to catch his dysentery.

136
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:28,400
And then spread it to the kids.
That's just what we need.

137
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:30,600
What happened? So your kids will catch it,
why are you panicking?

138
00:06:30,680 --> 00:06:34,000
How much can we be sick?
Really, they're always sick,

139
00:06:34,080 --> 00:06:36,240
and not alone. Either all together or one after another

140
00:06:36,320 --> 00:06:39,040
or in pairs.
-Okay, honey, come on, let's go to the balcony.

141
00:06:39,120 --> 00:06:40,400
There's good air for the germs out there.

142
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:41,600
To the balcony?
-Yeah, yeah.

143
00:06:41,680 --> 00:06:46,760
It's okay, it's not that bad.
Look, usually there's no problem

144
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:48,760
if someone here is sick at our house,
but today, you understand,

145
00:06:48,840 --> 00:06:52,520
there are happenings. You're not mad, right?
-No, why...

146
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:55,560
Okay, honey...
-What.

147
00:06:56,640 --> 00:06:58,920
Want me to heat up some bourekas with the majluf?
-Of course.

148
00:06:59,160 --> 00:07:01,320
Fine, but in the meantime, serve it to Meirav,

149
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:03,720
