150
00:07:04,320 --> 00:07:05,320
Okay, I'm going to check in with her.

151
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:08,960
Are you done eating?
-I'm not done, they're moving me to the balcony.

152
00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:10,320
I'll set up his food on the balcony.

153
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:12,200
Like Jason?
-Yeah, sweetie.

154
00:07:12,280 --> 00:07:14,240
Who's Jason?
-That's our dog,

155
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:16,120
he eats on the balcony.
-Dog...

156
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:17,600
At least you don't have to eat Bonzo.

157
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:20,000
Can we go to the kitchen now?

158
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:25,840
Dad, I didn't mean to drag him like that.
-Drag?

159
00:07:25,920 --> 00:07:27,880
To drag him, you need a crane.
-Oh, stop it.

160
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:30,760
Shabbat shalom.
-Shabbat shalom.

161
00:07:30,840 --> 00:07:32,840
Shabbat shalom.
-Shabbat shalom.

162
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:37,240
Oh, I see you took out the
computer today. You must be talking to Efrat.

163
00:07:37,320 --> 00:07:38,960
Yeah.
-No, no, no, but I want it to be a surprise.

164
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:41,760
No mention that Meirav and I are coming.
I want to call her from there, from the hotel.

165
00:07:41,840 --> 00:07:43,840
Wow, congratulations, I didn't tell you.
-What a coincidence.

166
00:07:43,920 --> 00:07:46,080
Wow, what's this? He knows you're not an actress, right?

167
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:48,640
Of course, that's the first thing I told him.
It just happened by chance.

168
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:52,440
But that's not... it, right?
-No, no, what are you talking about?

169
00:07:52,560 --> 00:07:55,160
I checked, everything, I asked. Serious production.

170
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:56,680
What, cool. So what, what are you playing? What's the role?

171
00:07:56,760 --> 00:07:59,640
Oh, it's without... talking.

172
00:08:00,440 --> 00:08:02,400
I'm playing the Israeli wife

173
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:05,600
of some guy involved
in some local corruption scandal.

174
00:08:05,680 --> 00:08:07,520
Something like... three days of shooting.

175
00:08:07,720 --> 00:08:09,760
But a week in Sinai.
-Yeah.

176
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:14,040
Why is Shai eating on the balcony?
-Shai is sick,

177
00:08:14,640 --> 00:08:16,760
and he shouldn't infect any of us.

178
00:08:16,840 --> 00:08:19,920
Wow, so I really need to keep
double the distance, because I really don't want

179
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:23,480
to miss this trip.
-Hey, Shabbat shalom.

180
00:08:24,840 --> 00:08:28,680
My sweet girl. I always knew
you could be a Hollywood actress.

181
00:08:28,760 --> 00:08:32,280
Okay, Mom, it’s not really a game.
Just a chance to meet Efrat.

182
00:08:32,520 --> 00:08:34,880
Perfect, just perfect.
-Too bad I can’t go.

183
00:08:35,559 --> 00:08:38,520
Speaking of which, Meirav is doing summary calls now.

184
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:40,520
Summary calls? What else is she doing?

185
00:08:41,919 --> 00:08:43,640
She’s sticking a goat in the house.

186
00:08:44,240 --> 00:08:49,120
If Meirav doesn’t come back from abroad,
she’s renting her room to her friend,

187
00:08:49,240 --> 00:08:52,360
I mean, she’s sticking a tenant here
in the house.

188
00:08:52,840 --> 00:08:55,120
What? But that’s not really her room,
you guys are the ones deciding.

189
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:57,160
Like what, did she tell you she’s a protected tenant?

190
00:08:57,240 --> 00:09:00,840
Yeah, yeah. What do we need
strangers in the house for?

191
00:09:01,080 --> 00:09:04,640
Just when I can finally
walk around freely in my own house.

192
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:06,240
In your underwear?
-Dad, come on.

193
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:08,880
Moshe, quick, say Moshe! So I can think about Moshe! Another one.

194
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:12,840
What? What, are you embarrassed to walk around in your underwear

195
00:09:12,920 --> 00:09:16,600
near the goat? What does she understand, goat. What... what...

196
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:24,280
Moshe, I get it.
-Come on, sis, what did I do to you?

197
00:09:24,480 --> 00:09:27,320
Are you kidding me?
-Come on, I’m so happy for you.

198
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:30,000
Amen, catch a millionaire,
send him some money back home.

199
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:33,000
Why amen?
-What, can’t I joke with you?

200
00:09:33,280 --> 00:09:36,120
That’s exactly the point, you guys always
joke about me, don’t support me

201
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:38,200
and don’t believe in me.
-We’re not joking about you-

202
00:09:38,280 --> 00:09:42,280
We’re just teasing you.
-That’s exactly what I wanted to talk to you about.

203
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:46,720
I get it, I want you to be a real brother,

204
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:50,200
someone who stands by me, supports me.

205
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:53,400
You were never there, not when it was bad

206
00:09:53,640 --> 00:09:54,800
and not when it was worse.

207
00:09:55,280 --> 00:09:58,600
What suddenly makes you want to
bring a stranger into the house? What suddenly?

208
00:09:58,680 --> 00:10:01,560
They’ll think! That we’re still dependent.
-Shh.

209
00:10:01,640 --> 00:10:03,320
Wait, you want her not to go,
to stay here?

210
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:07,440
Oh man, how that threat always comes up in the end.

211
00:10:07,520 --> 00:10:08,840
Oops, that’s in the conference.

212
00:10:10,120 --> 00:10:13,280
I thought it was over, that’s it,

213
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:17,480
I felt some kind of total release, some revolution,

214
00:10:18,160 --> 00:10:19,640
like Tahrir Square,

215
00:10:20,240 --> 00:10:21,720
!suddenly bam, scary.

216
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:25,960
Sali, enough. All we need
is to hope she finds her place there,

217
00:10:26,040 --> 00:10:28,320
and we’re here, the new tenant will manage.

218
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:31,840
I can’t deal with this computer.
Silvan, there’s some problem with the computer.

219
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:34,600
The computer has no problem, you have a problem.
-Two slaps on the board

220
00:10:34,720 --> 00:10:37,200
of his mom-mom and it works
like a horse. Is the bulletin ready?

221
00:10:37,800 --> 00:10:39,560
How was it in the principal's office?
-Tough.

222
00:10:39,640 --> 00:10:40,560
She gave me all negative feedback.

223
00:10:44,800 --> 00:10:46,720
Dad, Dad.
-Dad!

224
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:49,520
What, honey, what happened?

225
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:52,600
I finished eating and I want to go home, to rest.

226
00:10:53,240 --> 00:10:54,480
It’s cold here, it’s hot here,

227
00:10:54,720 --> 00:10:57,280
I’m not comfortable with this isolation. I want to go home.

228
00:10:57,360 --> 00:10:59,000
So what, you just came to eat and leave?

229
00:10:59,080 --> 00:11:02,640
You said you wouldn’t isolate me from your family
and look where I am?

230
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:04,520
Okay, what do you want me to tell your mom,

231
00:11:04,640 --> 00:11:06,120
that I left you home alone like a dog?

232
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:08,480
Sorry. I’m not...
-Sit.

233
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:15,120
I thought you understood computers better than me.

234
00:11:15,520 --> 00:11:17,800
What, I don’t?
-I talked to who.

235
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:21,320
Dad, it’s this stupid computer,
you need to replace it,

236
00:11:21,440 --> 00:11:23,800
it’s not that expensive.
-Girls, girls,

237
00:11:23,960 --> 00:11:26,760
you’re bothering Grandpa from concentrating.
-Yeah, girls, maybe you could go

238
00:11:27,040 --> 00:11:29,120
play somewhere else? Go out to the balcony.
-Ah ba ba ba...

239
00:11:29,240 --> 00:11:32,200
Shai’s on the balcony, you can’t go out there.
-Okay, I’ll take him from the balcony,

240
00:11:32,280 --> 00:11:36,000
so the girls can come in. Honey, come on,
the girls want to come into the balcony.

241
00:11:36,680 --> 00:11:40,960
Great, so can I go hide somewhere?
-Yeah, come on.

242
00:11:41,160 --> 00:11:42,400
To the bedroom?
-No, Meirav's in there.

243
00:11:42,480 --> 00:11:43,560
So?

244
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:45,920
I'll take you to the bathroom.
-How am I supposed to relax in the bath?

245
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:48,560
It’s just a few minutes.
-So bring me a pillow or something?

246
00:11:48,640 --> 00:11:50,720
Just put a roll of toilet paper
under your head, it’s comfy. Come on, babe.

247
00:11:50,800 --> 00:11:52,200
-What?

248
00:11:52,560 --> 00:11:53,760
-Here.

249
00:11:54,680 --> 00:11:57,040
Okay, fine. Can you come here for a sec?
-Yeah.

250
00:11:57,920 --> 00:12:00,120
Orna, I’m really hungry.
-Come on, let’s eat,

251
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:02,600
you can continue that later.
-Here, here. Here’s the problem.

252
00:12:03,080 --> 00:12:05,760
You forgot to turn on the screen.
-Oh.

253
00:12:05,880 --> 00:12:08,160
Did you see?
-Dad, can you buy a laptop today

254
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:09,200
for 300 bucks?

255
00:12:09,280 --> 00:12:10,800
With a camera inside.
-Right.

256
00:12:11,280 --> 00:12:14,720
Where am I supposed to get 300 bucks, come on?
That’s good enough, just drop it. It’s fine.

257
00:12:16,520 --> 00:12:18,560
Yeah, Meirav, I’m ready.
-Okay, don’t stress.

258
00:12:18,640 --> 00:12:21,320
I’m not stressing, come on, talk.
-I’m not saying anything.

259
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:23,520
Ah, Meirav, it’s not cool right now
for you to act all hurt.

260
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:27,080
I’m not going to beg you,
come on, Meirav, talk, Meirav, talk,

261
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:28,520
just talk already!

262
00:12:32,280 --> 00:12:36,960
So here’s the deal. Sit down, you probably already know

263
00:12:37,640 --> 00:12:39,600
that I’m leaving.

264
00:12:40,560 --> 00:12:43,520
The ticket for me is one-way,

265
00:12:44,240 --> 00:12:46,960
and I’m at a crossroads in my life.

266
00:12:47,760 --> 00:12:51,920
I’m leaving all my failures
and the...

267
00:12:52,400 --> 00:12:57,280
and the few successes behind,
and I want to start fresh.

268
00:12:57,640 --> 00:12:59,000
Great, you have my blessing.

269
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:04,040
But before I go, I wanted to tell you

270
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:07,680
a few words of criticism about your performance as a sister.

271
00:13:07,760 --> 00:13:09,720
Why just a few words? Come on, bottom line.

272
00:13:09,840 --> 00:13:12,840
Grade. What?
-That’s exactly what I wanted to tell you,

273
00:13:12,920 --> 00:13:14,600
that you never had patience for me.

274
00:13:15,560 --> 00:13:16,800
At least I’m consistent.

275
00:13:20,760 --> 00:13:23,480
Sorry to interrupt, but I think
you guys should first check

276
00:13:23,560 --> 00:13:25,360
who this girl is. Maybe she’s a kleptomaniac?

277
00:13:25,560 --> 00:13:27,640
They’ll take stuff from your house,
you won’t have a problem saying.

278
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:30,680
Anyway, make a proper contract with her.
-What a mess.

279
00:13:30,760 --> 00:13:33,800
For weeks, weeks I’ve been dreaming
of a man under his vine, a man under his fig tree

280
00:13:33,960 --> 00:13:35,360
and under his olive tree.

281
00:13:36,120 --> 00:13:37,960
Come on, why are you making such a big deal?

282
00:13:38,560 --> 00:13:40,800
We’ll try. If it doesn’t work out, we’ll tell you to leave.

283
00:13:40,880 --> 00:13:42,360
But she’ll also be a protected tenant.

284
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:45,240
Wait, is she also going to eat our food?
-It’ll stay, we won’t let her?

285
00:13:45,320 --> 00:13:47,160
Maybe it’s better if you write to me, I’ll put it in the freezer.

286
00:13:47,280 --> 00:13:49,160
There’s no room in the freezer. The freezer is full of leftovers.

287
00:13:49,360 --> 00:13:51,680
There are leftovers in the freezer?
-When was the last time you checked the freezer?

288
00:13:52,360 --> 00:13:55,680
Okay, who haven’t I talked to yet? Alin. Come here.

289
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:58,200
Miri gave me the main points.

290
00:13:59,280 --> 00:14:02,840
Okay. Orna! Has Moshe Katz arrived yet?
-In the kitchen.

291
00:14:03,880 --> 00:14:04,960
Orna!

292
00:14:06,640 --> 00:14:09,520
Psst, psst.
-Bismillah, you scared me. What’s up?

293
00:14:09,800 --> 00:14:12,400
You left me here.
-Left you? I didn’t leave.

294
00:14:12,480 --> 00:14:15,360
I thought you weren’t coming back.
Can we move?

295
00:14:15,520 --> 00:14:17,320
No. Not yet, not yet, babe.
Come on, let’s go to the bedroom,

296
00:14:17,400 --> 00:14:18,840
Meirav just cleared it out. Come on.
-Okay.

297
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:20,920
Slowly, slowly.

298
00:14:22,400 --> 00:14:24,960
Wow, I’m so excited I can’t eat.

299
00:14:25,040 --> 00:14:26,360
I can’t take a bite.

300
00:14:29,560 --> 00:14:32,640
Just so you know, Meirav, everything you achieve
in Hollywood will be thanks to me,

301
00:14:32,880 --> 00:14:35,840
Because I was the one who was supposed to go, not you.
-Thanks, Moshe.

302
00:14:36,320 --> 00:14:38,560
You've always been on guard.
-Thanks.

303
00:14:39,120 --> 00:14:41,160
Alright, I’m done here, I’m heading to the living room.

304
00:14:41,240 --> 00:14:42,080
But the summary...

305
00:14:43,200 --> 00:14:44,800
You'll have me for a week of summaries.

306
00:14:46,080 --> 00:14:46,920
So what,

307
00:14:48,680 --> 00:14:49,520
you’re leaving.

308
00:14:50,800 --> 00:14:53,760
I mean not coming back,
not that you know, God forbid.

309
00:14:55,080 --> 00:14:57,560
Why? For whom?

310
00:14:58,480 --> 00:15:02,440
And I also mean coming back,
not that you know, God forbid...

311
00:15:02,520 --> 00:15:05,920
So what exactly is your role there?
-I’m the hero's wife.

312
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:08,880
So you’re the heroine.
-No need to exaggerate.

313
00:15:08,960 --> 00:15:12,560
He’s the hero, I’ll be in the background,
it’s a small role.

314
00:15:12,640 --> 00:15:15,520
There’s a big rule that says: there are no small roles,

315
00:15:15,960 --> 00:15:19,440
only lousy actors.
-Dad...

316
00:15:20,200 --> 00:15:21,920
I would be so happy to go there.

317
00:15:22,440 --> 00:15:24,440
They don’t need some Russian spy there, like...

318
00:15:26,320 --> 00:15:27,160
How should I know?

319
00:15:28,480 --> 00:15:31,320
Have fun, my sister.
-And make sure Meirav doesn’t do anything stupid.

320
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:33,160
Find a groom!

321
00:15:33,240 --> 00:15:34,400
Amen.
-Amen.

322
00:15:36,040 --> 00:15:41,080
Sit down, my whole body is shaking,
my back is killing me from the bathtub.

323
00:15:41,680 --> 00:15:43,840
What? You were lying in the bathtub?
-You told me to.

324
00:15:44,040 --> 00:15:47,120
Well, I was joking with you.
-Sit down, I want to go home, now.

325
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:51,440
The illness could still get complicated.
There are cases that ended in death.

326
00:15:51,520 --> 00:15:55,760
No, no, no. Death isn’t a fool.
It comes to those who least expect it.

327
00:15:56,360 --> 00:15:59,480
What? What does that mean? That my mom
and your grandma will never die?

328
00:16:00,560 --> 00:16:02,920
You know you’re irresponsible
and a first-class egoist?

329
00:16:04,480 --> 00:16:07,040
What happened? I thought we finished the conversation.
-I haven’t finished.

330
00:16:07,480 --> 00:16:09,920
Aren’t you ashamed to bring your sick husband here?
You want him to infect me

331
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:13,120
with his germs so I can’t go abroad
and because of that, I won’t get married?

332
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:15,880
Now you’ve figured out my evil plan.

333
00:16:17,840 --> 00:16:19,320
Oh-my-God!

334
00:16:21,360 --> 00:16:24,280
Why would a kid living with his parents
rent his room to someone else?

335
00:16:24,480 --> 00:16:26,120
Don’t agree to that.
-It’s not that simple.

336
00:16:26,200 --> 00:16:28,480
To make sure she’s not a protected tenant,
you have to make a contract

337
00:16:28,560 --> 00:16:31,960
for every child over 18. Otherwise
one day you’ll find yourselves on the street.

338
00:16:32,280 --> 00:16:36,120
I wouldn’t be surprised if she says she
didn’t agree with Meirav on which room

339
00:16:36,200 --> 00:16:39,520
to choose for the son as the bedroom.
Then she’ll bring a lawyer,

340
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:44,120
and we’ll have to sleep in the fridge.
-Sali, you’re exaggerating again,

341
00:16:44,200 --> 00:16:46,320
you’re already sleeping in the fridge.
-Maybe I’ll go with Orna

342
00:16:46,400 --> 00:16:47,920
and then the girls can stay here with Meirav.

343
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:50,320
No, no.
-No, no. Let her go and enjoy.

344
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:53,160
Yeah. Anyway, let her take her time too.

345
00:16:53,720 --> 00:16:55,640
Maybe Meirav will even come back with me after a week?

346
00:16:55,720 --> 00:16:58,520
Why? Why always think the worst? Why?

347
00:16:59,560 --> 00:17:02,760
Dad, imagine you’re running to the bathroom with a stomach ache.

348
00:17:02,840 --> 00:17:04,680
Suddenly the new tenant, let’s call her Aleph for example,

349
00:17:05,119 --> 00:17:07,119
is stuck in the bathroom with her own stomach ache,

350
00:17:07,839 --> 00:17:08,760
and you’re under pressure.

351
00:17:09,240 --> 00:17:11,480
Wait, is the tenant Aleph from the tourism office?

352
00:17:11,560 --> 00:17:14,000
Aleph from the president's office or Aleph from the top of the police?

353
00:17:14,079 --> 00:17:15,920
Aleph.
-Stop.

354
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:18,440
No, there’s no limit to Shabi’s chutzpah,
and you’re still approving it.

355
00:17:18,520 --> 00:17:21,720
Since she was a little girl,
you always let her do whatever she wanted.

356
00:17:21,880 --> 00:17:23,119
Dad, come.
-Yeah, sure.

357
00:17:25,760 --> 00:17:27,920
What, to connect?
-Yeah, just need to send her a text,

358
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:29,640
so she can connect too.
-What time is it there now?

359
00:17:29,760 --> 00:17:31,440
It’s ten hours behind. How much is that?

360
00:17:31,640 --> 00:17:33,040
Wait.
-Seven in the morning.

361
00:17:34,040 --> 00:17:36,400
So, is she awake already?
-She has kids. She's awake.

362
00:17:39,120 --> 00:17:41,520
Ah, there you go. That's how it is.

363
00:17:42,120 --> 00:17:43,640
Dad...
-M'r... Meirav.

364
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:45,440
Just a second.
-What?

365
00:17:45,640 --> 00:17:47,480
Meirav, my dear,

366
00:17:47,600 --> 00:17:50,280
You know I love you very, very much, right?

367
00:17:51,080 --> 00:17:54,480
I want you to know that I'm
really, really sorry you're leaving us

368
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:58,400
for good.
-Not sure it's for good.

369
00:18:00,320 --> 00:18:02,160
Never, Meirav, it's allowed,

370
00:18:02,280 --> 00:18:04,360
you should never lose hope.

371
00:18:04,960 --> 00:18:05,880
Please
huh?

372
00:18:05,960 --> 00:18:07,160
Okay.
-Amen.

373
00:18:07,240 --> 00:18:11,720
So that's it, why would you leave with a bitter taste in your mouth?

374
00:18:12,320 --> 00:18:15,280
Why bitter?
-This tenant,

375
00:18:15,360 --> 00:18:19,400
that you brought into the house, it's really uncomfortable for us.

376
00:18:19,800 --> 00:18:21,400
You understand? Suddenly, she's like this...

377
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:25,520
I thought the 300 dollars
could really help you guys

378
00:18:25,640 --> 00:18:28,240
with all the expenses.
-300?

379
00:18:29,960 --> 00:18:33,520
No, no, what... what does...
what do you mean 300 dollars?

380
00:18:33,680 --> 00:18:36,520
What? What are you talking about?
I didn't quite understand.

381
00:18:36,600 --> 00:18:38,320
Mom didn't tell you?
-No.

382
00:18:38,520 --> 00:18:41,920
She'll pay 600 dollars
and we'll split it fifty-fifty.

383
00:18:42,520 --> 00:18:46,200
Oh, really? 300 dollars? That she's...

384
00:18:46,600 --> 00:18:47,960
That's really not feasible.

385
00:18:50,080 --> 00:18:52,840
Wait, is that every month?
-Yeah.

386
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:54,120
What, what are you saying?

387
00:18:55,640 --> 00:18:57,520
Suddenly, I'm thinking this is really,

388
00:18:58,280 --> 00:19:02,040
having a subletter live with me is even...
it's even great for me.

389
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:03,240
You get it?

390
00:19:04,120 --> 00:19:06,480
Is the computer working at all?
-Yeah, I fixed it. You can connect.

391
00:19:06,680 --> 00:19:08,880
She's connecting.
-Come on, hurry up, connect.

392
00:19:08,960 --> 00:19:10,640
I miss you.
-Maybe we should call Shai?

393
00:19:10,840 --> 00:19:11,840
No!
-No!

394
00:19:11,920 --> 00:19:13,040
I don't feel like a mambo.

395
00:19:13,320 --> 00:19:14,440
Okay, I'll make us some tea soon.

396
00:19:24,440 --> 00:19:26,440
Efrat, Shabbat Shalom.
-Hi

397
00:19:27,120 --> 00:19:32,400
Shabbat Shalom, how's everyone?
-Shabbat Shalom. Everyone's doing great.

398
00:19:32,520 --> 00:19:35,720
Everyone here misses you, my sweet.

399
00:19:36,040 --> 00:19:37,040
Okay, Mom, no need to shout.

400
00:19:37,440 --> 00:19:40,920
Dad, you need a new camera for the computer.
-No problem, no problem. Okay.

401
00:19:41,520 --> 00:19:44,080
What's up, babe?
-Sit down, babe,

402
00:19:44,160 --> 00:19:46,960
when are you coming to visit? I miss you so much,

403
00:19:47,120 --> 00:19:50,640
I miss all of you.
-Don't worry, we'll meet soon.

404
00:19:51,120 --> 00:19:53,080
Shh.
-What shh?

405
00:19:53,160 --> 00:19:55,160
No, nothing. Nothing. What's going on with you?

406
00:19:55,640 --> 00:19:58,480
Honestly, not much. Because of the movie
they made about that guy from Facebook

407
00:19:58,720 --> 00:20:01,320
now they're making all kinds of movies
like that about the tech world,

408
00:20:02,280 --> 00:20:06,560
and there's this disgusting yellow channel
making a movie about Mike,

409
00:20:06,640 --> 00:20:09,520
a not-so-flattering film. They're starting to shoot it this week,

410
00:20:09,800 --> 00:20:12,600
and we're afraid it will hurt his business. I don't want that.

411
00:20:13,280 --> 00:20:14,520
-What?

412
00:20:15,040 --> 00:20:18,280
They're filming a yellow movie about my husband, Mike.

413
00:20:19,280 --> 00:20:20,720
Who knows who will play me.

414
00:20:21,080 --> 00:20:24,960
They'll never find! Someone as pretty as me, Efrat.
-What a shame, babe.

415
00:20:25,080 --> 00:20:26,320
No, they didn't even write her a big role.

416
00:20:26,960 --> 00:20:29,120
Otherwise, only Penelope Cruz would fit.

417
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:32,280
But I read the script, it's not a role with lines,

418
00:20:32,720 --> 00:20:35,320
like I'm his puppet. What nonsense.

419
00:20:35,520 --> 00:20:38,200
Sure, you know,
they'll bring some Israeli who looks like,

420
00:20:38,400 --> 00:20:40,840
more or less like me, the poor thing won't know.

421
00:20:40,920 --> 00:20:44,080
She's in a racist movie
about a Jew robbing Americans.

422
00:20:44,160 --> 00:20:46,440
Oh, oh, oh.
-No, no. Don't take it too hard.

423
00:20:46,520 --> 00:20:49,800
Mike has the best lawyers
there are, everything's fine.

424
00:20:50,160 --> 00:20:52,960
Gisele! Rachel and Yael are still sleeping.
Maybe I should wake them up.

425
00:20:53,120 --> 00:20:54,200
No, no. Don't wake them.

426
00:20:54,280 --> 00:20:57,040
Not Yael and not Rachel.

427
00:20:57,400 --> 00:20:58,840
You ruined my Shabbat.

428
00:20:58,920 --> 00:21:00,720
Bye, sweetie.
-Kisses.

429
00:21:02,400 --> 00:21:03,600
You're not doing that to her.

430
00:21:03,840 --> 00:21:05,960
It doesn't have to be the same movie at all.

431
00:21:06,960 --> 00:21:08,400
Hollywood is big, it's not Migdal HaEmek.

432
00:21:09,800 --> 00:21:11,400
I decided to walk.
-No, no, honey, come on.

433
00:21:11,480 --> 00:21:12,680
I'll take you home, come on.
-Really?

434
00:21:13,160 --> 00:21:14,760
It's okay, you can stay.
I won't make it to the flight anyway.

435
00:21:14,840 --> 00:21:17,120
Shabbat Shalom. Strong, blessed.

436
00:21:18,640 --> 00:21:20,960
From now on, everyone blame Efrat

437
00:21:21,040 --> 00:21:22,080
for me being single.

438
00:21:22,840 --> 00:21:24,520
Shabbat Shalom.
-No.

439
00:21:24,680 --> 00:21:25,720
I have immunity.

440
00:21:26,680 --> 00:21:29,920
Enough, the $300 for the computer is gone.
-Silvan...

441
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:32,360
Stay away from me! Stay away from me!

442
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:35,120
Honey, turn off the AC. I'm cold.

443
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:37,440
Come on, honey, it's on heat. What's wrong with you?

444
00:21:37,520 --> 00:21:38,560
Why do you act like this when you're sick?

445
00:21:40,360 --> 00:21:41,200
Yes, Mom.

446
00:21:41,280 --> 00:21:42,640
Shiko, you're sick.

447
00:21:42,720 --> 00:21:45,640
Oh, you sound terrible. Are they taking good care of you?

448
00:21:45,720 --> 00:21:47,200
Yes, Mom, yes.

449
00:21:47,280 --> 00:21:49,560
What meds are you taking? What did the doctor prescribe?

450
